== Pork ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Pat @pork tenderloin{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @za'atar spice{1/2%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add pork and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan. Roast on top rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Saucy Tomato Pan Sauce ==

While pork roasts, wash and dry produce. Trim, peel, and dice @carrots{6%ounce} into ¼-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons. Quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @dill{1/4%ounce}. Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} (use #medium pot{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add carrots, half the garlic, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and half the @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer and cover. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cucumber Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and pepper, and as much dill as you like. Stir until fully combined.

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic; cook, pressing tomato slightly, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1/3 cup water (2/3 cup for 4 servings). Cook, stirring constantly and scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until sauce is thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== Finish and Serve ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide couscous, pork, and salad between plates. Spoon pan sauce over pork. Garnish with any remaining dill and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.